arking a clear cultural demarcation from the theatrical output of the early seventeenth century, the Restoration is constantly reflecting back on the previous thirty years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish dramay17th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aTheaterxHistoryy17th centuryzGreat Britain. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Drama.2bisacsh  aCharles I.  aCharles II.  aCommonwealth.  aDrama.  aEnglish Civil War.  aInterregnum.  aOliver Cromwell.  aPlaytext.  aProtectorate.  aRepublic.1 aWillie, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499676540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784996765423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784996765/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles